<p>
  Fix sideways photos, create mirror effects, or correct scanned documents with the free Image Rotate & Flip tool — all in your browser, no upload required.
</p>

<h2>How to Rotate an Image Online</h2>

<ol>
  <li>Open the <a href="/imagewonder/image-rotate-flip">Image Rotate & Flip</a> tool.</li>
  <li>Drop your image or click to browse.</li>
  <li>Click <strong>Rotate 90° CW</strong> or <strong>Rotate 90° CCW</strong> to rotate.</li>
  <li>Click multiple times for 180° or 270°.</li>
  <li>Click <strong>Download</strong> to save.</li>
</ol>

<a href="/imagewonder/image-rotate-flip" class="tool-cta">
  <div class="cta-label">Free Tool</div>
  <div class="cta-title">Image Rotate & Flip — One-Click Transform →</div>
  <div class="cta-desc">Rotate 90°/180°/270°, flip horizontal or vertical. Live preview, instant PNG download. No upload, no account.</div>
</a>

<h2>Rotate on Windows</h2>

<p>Right-click any image in File Explorer → <strong>Rotate right</strong> or <strong>Rotate left</strong>. This rotates by 90° and saves in place (overwrites the original). For more control, use the browser tool above.</p>

<h2>Rotate on Mac</h2>

<ol>
  <li>Open in <strong>Preview</strong>.</li>
  <li>Go to <strong>Tools → Rotate Left/Right</strong>.</li>
  <li>Save the file.</li>
</ol>

<h2>Rotate on iPhone</h2>

<ol>
  <li>Open in <strong>Photos</strong> → tap <strong>Edit</strong>.</li>
  <li>Tap the crop/rotate icon → use the rotate button (top-left).</li>
  <li>Tap <strong>Done</strong>.</li>
</ol>

<h2>Flip vs Rotate — What's the Difference?</h2>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Rotate:</strong> Turns the image clockwise or counter-clockwise. The image is the same but seen from a different angle.</li>
  <li><strong>Flip Horizontal (mirror):</strong> Creates a left-right mirror image. Useful for text on clothing mockups, profile poses, and symmetry effects.</li>
  <li><strong>Flip Vertical:</strong> Creates an upside-down mirror. Used for reflection effects in design and photography.</li>
</ul>

